definitions.definition: The quality of being manoeuvrable ; ability to be manoeuvred .
examples: Articulated buses were invented to improve the manoeuvrability of long buses capable of carrying a large number of passengers.

definitions.definition: Ability to manoeuvre; ability to carry out a manoeuvre or strategic plan.
examples: My manoeuvrability is limited. I don't have many options left.

main_definition: ( British spelling ) The quality of being manoeuvrable ; ability to be manoeuvred .
secondary_definitions: Ability to manoeuvre; ability to carry out a manoeuvre or strategic plan.
